# Core Rules - Always Follow

- Use vanilla Javascript/HTML5/CSS
- Keep code simple, readable, and modular. Prefer small focused functions.
- Use descriptive names. Avoid abbreviations unless obvious.
- Add clear comments for complex audio sync / Web Audio / YouTube IFrame logic.
- Error handling: Graceful degradation, meaningful console messages, user-friendly alerts.
- State management: Keep it lightweight (no heavy frameworks unless necessary).
- Performance: Be mindful of audio memory usage and sync drift.
- Style: Consistent formatting, clean imports, no unused code.
- Architecture: Separate concerns — UI, audio recording, sync engine, storage.